    secure, and distributed applications. It provides built-in support for high-volume transactions, scalability, and robust security that standard editions

9) What tools or APIs are included in Java EE?
-->Java EE (Enterprise Edition) includes a comprehensive set of APIs and specifications designed for developing large-scale, distributed enterprise applications.
    These technologies have since been transitioned to the Jakarta EE project under the Eclipse Foundation, where the APIs use the jakarta.* namespace instead of javax.*.


10) What happened to Java EE when Oracle handed it over to Eclipse Foundation?
-->When Oracle handed Java EE over to the Eclipse Foundation, it was renamed Jakarta EE and transitioned to an open,
    community-driven development model to foster faster innovation, particularly for cloud-native applications
